text: Donie O'Sullivan (Irish: Dónal Ó Súilleabháin) (born 1940 in Killarney, County Kerry) is a former Irish sportsperson. He played Gaelic football with his local club Spa and was a member of the Kerry senior inter-county team from 1962 until 1975. He was Kerry's first All Star in 1971 and won a second in 1972. ==References== Category:1940 births Category:Living people Category:All- Ireland-winning captains (football) Category:Alumni of University College Dublin Category:Irish schoolteachers Category:Spa Gaelic footballers Category:Dr Crokes Gaelic footballers Category:UCD Gaelic footballers Category:Kerry inter-county Gaelic footballers Category:Munster inter- provincial Gaelic footballers
